(1,	69,	'Tinhvan received certificate of Top 10 ICT enterprises in e-Government field',	'On December 14, 2020 evening, Tinhvan was honored to receive the certificate of Top 10 Vietnam ICT Enterprises 2020 in e-Government field awarded by Vietnam Software And IT Services Association ( VINASA). The announcement ceremony of Top 10 ICT Enterprises took place within the framework of the event of “Vietnam DX Day 2020”.',	'<p>On December 14, 2020 evening, Tinhvan was honored to receive the certificate of Top 10 Vietnam ICT Enterprises 2020 in e-Government field awarded by Vietnam Software And IT Services Association ( VINASA). The announcement ceremony of Top 10 ICT Enterprises took place within the framework of the event of &ldquo;Vietnam DX Day 2020&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants that attended and awarded the certificates, honored selected enterprises were Mr. Nguyen Thien Nhan &ndash; Politburo member, 12th&nbsp;Party Central Committee; Mr. Phan Xuan Dung &ndash; Member of the Party Central Committee, Member of the National Assembly Standing Committee, Chairman of the National Assembly&rsquo;s Committee on Science and Technology; Mr. Nguyen Quan &ndash; Former Minister of Science and Technology; Mr. Pham Tan Cong &ndash; Deputy Secretary of Party Committee of Central Enterprises Bloc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Out of the 15 newly announced fields receiving the title of &ldquo;Top 10 ICT Enterprises 2020&rdquo;, there were only 5 out of 15 fields selecting enough 10 typical enterprises, including the following fields: software export enterprise; Enterprise that provides e-government solutions; Enterprise that provides digital transformation platform; Enterprise that provides digital transformation services and solutions; ICT service enterprise. In particular, according to the statistics of the Organizing Committee, more than 80% of participating enterprises have been researching and applying new technologies of Industry 4.0 in the process of developing products and solutions; Total revenue in 2019 of Top 10 Enterprises accounted for more than 76% of total revenue of Vietnam&rsquo;s ICT industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the representative of the Organizing Committee, selected enterprises of the Program will be introduced in the special publication &ldquo;Top 10 Vietnam ICT Enterprises 2020&Prime; released in 3 languages: English, Japanese, Vietnamese. These enterprises will be directly introduced to more than 2,000 domestic agencies and units, more than 10,000 partners from nearly 100 economies around the world in VINASA&rsquo;s international cooperation network, and be introduced and accompanied in major events of Vietnam&rsquo;s ICT industry, trade promotion programs participating in world&rsquo;s leading exhibitions and conferences in key markets of US, Japan, Europe, Korea, Australia &hellip; &ldquo;More importantly, this is a core force in digital transformation programs for agencies and enterprises and is also typical representatives of Vietnam&rsquo;s ICT industry to welcome the wave of opportunities to enter the global value chain&rdquo;, emphasized by the Organizing Committee representative.</p>',	'en',	1,	'2021-05-27 13:23:08',	'2021-05-28 14:53:21',	'',	'',	'',	'',	''),
